<br>
wayne<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#F9FBFD><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=howardsmith@flyfishingarkansasandmissouri>Howard Smith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#000000>(9/8/03 5:59 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> re</span><hr size=1> I do.  Hate gettin' caught without a leader when I need it. Since there are no fly shopps locally and I'm usually on the river early, I just tie my own.  I also tie some for special reasons, you just can't always buy what you want. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFFF><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/bflyfishingarkansasandmissouri.showUserPublicProfile?gid=flynut62>flynut62</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 22<br> <font color=#000000>(9/8/03 8:24 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/fflyfishingarkansasandmissourifrm14.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=157.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re</span><hr size=1> I have had people tell me that buying tapered leaders is better because you wont have all those knots . . . But I am realizing that I always have 2 to 3 knots in mine anyways. I buy 4x leaders, sanp the tippet off and add 5x and 6x to get what I want. Therefore 2 knots minimum all the time. If I go to 7x like I did this Saturday, then it's 3! So what's a few more knots . . ? :-)  With me buying for 3 fisher(people) it gets expensive.<br>
<br>
I think I'll give it a shot . . .<br>
<br>
wayne<br>
<br>
